SUMMARY:Fabric Data Engineering with Python Notebooks
DESCRIPTION:Cloud Data Driven\nDid you know that spark notebooks and data 
 flows generation 2.0 are more costly than python notebooks? As a small com
 pany how can you do more with a small capacity?\n\nI will be talking about
  Python notebooks in this session. Libraries such as Polars\, Delta Lake\,
  Duck DB and MS SQL are available to the designer to extract\, transform a
 nd load data.\n\nAt the end of this talk\, you will understand how to use 
 the Capacity Metrics application to compare different data engineering des
 igns and fine the most cost effective solution for your company.
